The team also lost to the Knicks in their NBA Cup game, with Joel Embiid making his season debut. The Sixers are hoping to secure their second win against the Hornets before Embiid returns. name: Spurs
summary: The San Antonio Spurs have experienced a flurry of recent developments, including a medical emergency for coach Gregg Popovich, who suffered a mild stroke, and the emergence of rookie Stephon Castle. Despite Popovich's absence, interim coach Mitch Johnson has led the team to a 139-130 victory over the Washington Wizards, with rookie Victor Wembanyama recording a remarkable 50 points and 7 blocks. However, the Spurs also suffered a setback with a loss to the Sacramento Kings. Johnson's performance as fill-in coach has received mixed reviews, with some grading him positively while others have highlighted Wembanyama's contributions. The Spurs' coaching situation remains fluid, with Johnson holding the reins for the time being while Popovich recovers.

name: Emilia perez
summary: Various news outlets have shared their verdicts on the recently released film "Emilia Pérez." TIME Magazine applauds the film as an "exuberant ode to human possibility." NPR highlights the film's transgender protagonist and its message of empowerment. The New York Times praises its "song and dance of transformation." However, The New Yorker finds it "incurious" and "cis nonsense." Autostraddle commends its uniqueness. Netflix Tudum explores the film's ending, while USA TODAY hails it as "the most wildly original film" of 2024. PEOPLE magazine delves into its inspiration, and Vulture questions whether Netflix's mainstream audience is ready for such an unconventional film. Slate Magazine praises the film as a "wild" and "one of the best" of the year. Overall, the film has garnered mixed reactions, with some critics praising its originality and others finding it uninspired.
